<subSubSection id="56532EF00BD398518721E9FB384050CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="notes">
<paragraph id="DDEEFFEB2F595A92929563F35A40880C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C8FD609993B6F8AA171878DEEE4B585" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation id="756961622C690A84D92B492A12FC503F" author="Jordon, CTA" journalOrPublisher="Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="140 - 448" refId="B15" refString="Jordon, CTA, 1855. Notice sur plusieurs plantes novelles. Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne 2: 140 - 448" title="Notice sur plusieurs plantes novelles." volume="2" year="1855">Jordon (1855)</bibRefCitation>
cited the following five collections: the Jura sur le Reculet (Ain), and Mont Ventoux, in August 1841, 
<emphasis id="BD43EBDC0A64B40B7B0E8B58274EAA97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. Jordan</emphasis>
; Mt. St-Nizier near Grenoble, 
<emphasis id="73519D55236ACED41869A1EA0DE4EB97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Verlot</emphasis>
; Bex (canton of Vaud), 
<emphasis id="09CD0991A28569A0F75AC42D3960FA3A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">E. Thomas</emphasis>
; Mt. St-Nizier near Grenoble, 
<emphasis id="1FCEBE194DFA65FC763124707458AF94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Clement</emphasis>
. Also cited is a report of Reuter of his collection from Jura sur le Reculet [P-03161256, image!], and 
<taxonomicName id="6AED1737E79298045A44941DFBDC0DED" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis filiformis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis id="90F76870C9D8481132C72963302B754E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Agrostis filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<emphasis id="98321006011EC679AD33897067ABFCF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Vill</emphasis>
. We select The 
<emphasis id="A01099D3F80CBEE7233BF7FBAC2E6F1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Verlot 1584</emphasis>
specimen as there are several duplicates, and P-03161255 as the lectotype because that sheet is not mounted with any other collection as the MPU and BM sheets seem to be.
</paragraph>
